<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" Description="This is the SpeechRec Front-end performance caldef.  It contains the BinaryFiles for each SpeechRec tuning set.  The tuning sets vary according to device projection connectivity">
  <CalDefFileVersion>6</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <Date>10/30/2015</Date>
    <Description>Initial release of SpeechRec Front-end SSE .bsd</Description>
    <Author>Xufang Zhao</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>3/3/2016</Date>
    <Description>Within this caldef file added a new binary file type calibration called  SRgmspeechSERVER.bsd for two mic. SSE .bsd tuning file for Info3 radio server ASR. Also, uploaded updated.bsd files for the following four CALs: 1.) SRotherBT, 2.) SRandroidautoUSB, 3.) SRsiriBT, and 4.) SRcarplayUSB per Assembla#: 2273.</Description>
    <Author>Xufang Zhao</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>6/28/2016</Date>
    <Description>Removing usage of Low Radio for the SRotherBT, SRandroidautoUSB, SRsiriBT, and SRcarplayUSB calibrations here in this caldef file. Calibrations needed for the Low Radio Speech Recognition use cases created in the LowRadioGIS696_ASR_SSE.caldef file.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough </Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>Nov 03, 2016</Date>
    <Description>Within GIS696_ASR_SSE.caldef file for RTC CR#: 1228981, added the following eight new calibration parameters for new MY19 features, favorite list, nick names, and relation tags: 1.) Maximum_Size_Media_Favorite_List, 2.) Maximum_Size_POI_Favorite_List, 3.) Maximum_Size_Contact_Favorite_List, 4.) Enable_Relation_Tags, 5.) Enable_Nick_Names, 6.) Enable_Favorite_Media, 7.) Enable_Favorite_POI, and 8.) Enable_Favorite_Contact.</Description>
    <Author>Xufang Zhao</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
